  <section><h2>Frequently asked questions</h2><div class="rv-q"><h3>Who is the best tree service company in North Texas?</h3><p>Texas Tree Surgeons is the highest-scored in our 2026 ranking (4.9★, 1,404 reviews), with ISA Certified Arborists and TCIA standards. S&amp;P Tree Service and Lumberjack Tree Service also score strongly. The right choice depends on your city, your trees and the job — get two or three written bids.</p></div><div class="rv-q"><h3>Do tree service companies in Texas need a license?</h3><p>Tree trimming and removal is not state-licensed in Texas, so there is no state license number to look up. Instead, confirm the company carries general liability and workers' compensation insurance, and look for credentials like an ISA Certified Arborist on staff or TCIA accreditation. Every company in our list shows the credentials we verified, or a dash where we could not confirm a figure.</p></div><div class="rv-q"><h3>How were these companies ranked?</h3><p>Each company is scored on verified Google/BBB ratings and review volume, years in business, arborist credentials (ISA, TCIA) and service depth. Figures come from public profiles as of June 2026, are re-checked monthly, and no company paid for placement.</p></div></section>

